Commands we should run to setup allure report

1. Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser
irm get.scoop.sh | iex

2. scope install allure

If still allure fails then try this

3. \bin\checkver.ps1 allure -u

4. scope update allure

Now to run allure in pytest use Terminal and add this in last

--aluredir="/allureReport"

After the test there will be multiple files will be created in the allureReport folder
If u want a report than follow this command -

allure serve allureRepport